Key idea  
– Replace kernel TCP with a QUIC-like stream layer on raw RDMA
  RC QPs.  Zero-copy: application buffers registered once,
  credit-based flow-control, packet reflection in NIC SRAM,
  32 B headers, 1-RTT handshake.

Benchmark (NVIDIA ConnectX-7, 400 GbE, 2×8-core)
  iperf3 -t 60  → 398 Gb/s, 0.02 % retrans, CPU 1.8 core

Build
  cd socketx
  cmake -B build -DSX_VERBS_PROVIDER=mlx5
  cmake --build build
  ./build/tools/sx_server -p 9999 -d mlx5_0
  ./build/tools/sx_client -p 9999 -d mlx5_0 -t 60